<TITLE> BNP calls half-day hartal in Bogra </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, May 5 (bdnews24.com)  BNP has called a half-day strike on Sunday at Bogra in protest against the death of a local leader. Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir, the main opposition's senior joint secretary general, announced the strike when he visited Zakir's village in Garidaha Union under Sherpur Upazila in Bogra to express his condolences. The call came as a protest against the death of a local leader in a clash with Bangladesh Chhatra League activists at Singra Upazila in Natore. Zakir Hossain, a union-level leader of Bogra BNP, died from injuries he had sustained in a clash with Bangladesh Chhatra League activists at Singra. He died on his way to the hospital at around 4pm, witnesses said. A statement from the BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain said the ruling Awami League's student wing had attacked and killed one BNP leader and injured about 100 others. The clash at Singra was sparked when BCL activists attacked two buses at Singra bus stand bound for the BNP rally in Rajshahi, which BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia later addressed. Abul Kalam Azad, officer in charge of the Singra Police Station, told bdnews24.com that at around 11 am the BCL activists were holding a rally at the bus terminal. As two buses from Bogra, bound for the BNP rally, appeared the activists tried to take the banners from the buses. After a heated argument, the two groups of supporters began to fight each other, he said. The Awami League supporters also vandalised three decorated gates built on the Dhaka-Natore highway on Tuesday night. BCL activists burnt down two gates at Telbaria of Sadar Upazila around 11pm on Tuesday. bdn
